    "body_text": [
        {
            "text": "The new severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) coronavirus-2 (SARS-CoV2) may cause pneumonia and severe disease in high risk patients [1] . Since March 2020, has been declared a pandemic by the World Health Organization, with reported cases in most of the countries worldwide [2] . To date, compelling data strongly indicate that the severity and adverse progression of COVID-19 is related to older age and underlying conditions, primarily diabetes, obesity, and hypertension [3] [4] [5] , i.e. conditions forming the spectrum of the metabolic syndrome [6] .",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 136,
                    "end": 139,
                    "text": "[1]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF0"
                },
                {
                    "start": 278,
                    "end": 281,
                    "text": "[2]",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF1"
                },
                {
                    "start": 478,
