            "text": "important example of such crucial services in the context of diabetes, is the management of patients with acute and severe presentations of diabetes foot disease/ulcers. In the Journal of Diabetes and Its Complications, a relevant paper has been published on the surgical treatment of diabetic foot ulcers during the COVID-19 pandemic in China [14]. Based on the relevant local experiences and guidelines in China (i.e. the first epicenter of the COVID-19 pandemic), Tao et al. describe a \"double triage, double buffer, and dual mode\" model and the process for treatment of diabetic foot ulcers which was followed in the Renmin Hospital of Wuhan University during the COVID-19",
